                    <h2><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-exclamation-sign"> The Problem</span></h2>
                    <p>Lobbying is dominated by corporate backed groups who seek to further their own agenda and increase profits. Although we live in a representative democracy, public engagement in politics is disappointingly low as the branches of government struggle to directly communicate with the public. Most people are not properly informed regarding various enacted bills which directly affect their overall lives, and even if they were aware of various relevant bills, the tools to voice their opinion and promote change are non-existent. </p>

                    <button class="btn btn-success ">More</button>

                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok-circle"> The Solution</span></h2>
                    <p>Providing users with easily understandable news regarding general politics, and the implications of certain bills. Offering the ability to debate with other members of the Lobby community and participate in polls. Supplying users with the ability to create petitions and a social media integrated platform to easily rally support. </p>

                    <button class="btn btn-success ">More</button>

                </div>


                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-road"> Our Mission</span></h2>
                    <p>We do not believe in making the public pay for access to nation changing tools. Therefore, all functions of Lobby will be free and will remain free to the public. Our goal is to allow people to positively influnce the government, in a myriad of ways, by giving them the tools necessary to do so.</p>

